Endpoints.Name: getOpenIdConfiguration
Endpoints.Description:
Returns the OpenID Connect discovery configuration for the specified realm `{externalId}`.
Includes key endpoints for authorization, token issuance, introspection, user info, and logout.
Endpoints.Summary: Retrieve OpenID Connect Configuration for a Realm

200.Name: response200
200.Description: Successful retrieval of OpenID Connect configuration.

Response.Name: response
Response.Description: Successful retrieval of OpenID Connect configuration.

Parameters.Name: externalId
Parameters.Description: The unique external ID of the realm (e.g., "partner", "customer-xyz").

Endpoints.Name: authenticateDataHolder
Endpoints.Description:
Authenticate using the OAuth2 `client_credentials` grant type.
Returns an access token for system-level (non-user) API access.
Endpoints.Summary: Authenticate as a Data Holder (Client Credentials Flow)

Parameters.Name: externalId
Parameters.Description: The unique external ID of the realm (e.g., "partner", "customer-xyz").

Endpoints.Name: retrieveImpersonatedUserToken
Endpoints.Description:
Requests a new access token that acts on behalf of the specified user.
The returned token (`user_access_token`) must be used for all subsequent API calls requiring user context.
Endpoints.Summary: Retrieve an Impersonated User Access Token

200.Name: response200
200.Description: Successfully issued a user-context access token.

Response.Name: response
Response.Description: Successfully issued a user-context access token.

Parameters.Name: user_id
Parameters.Description: The unique identifier of the user you wish to impersonate.

Endpoints.Name: listConsents
Endpoints.Description:
Retrieves a list of all active and historical consents associated with the authenticated user or system.
Supports optional filtering by status and pagination.

Parameters.Name: status
Parameters.Description: Filter consents by status (e.g., ACTIVE, REVOKED, EXPIRED).

Parameters.Name: limit
Parameters.Description: Maximum number of results to return (default is 50).

Parameters.Name: offset
Parameters.Description: Number of records to skip for pagination.

TestCases.Name: Test listConsents
TestCases.Description:
Retrieves a list of all active and historical consents associated with the authenticated user or system.
Supports optional filtering by status and pagination.

Endpoints.Name: getConsent
Endpoints.Description: Retrieves detailed information about a specific consent using its `consentId`.

Parameters.Name: consentId
Parameters.Description: The unique identifier for the consent.

Endpoints.Name: revokeConsent
Endpoints.Description:
Revokes the specified consent. 

After revocation, the associated user data access permissions are removed, and any tokens granted under this consent will become invalid.

204.Name: response204
204.Description: Consent successfully revoked. No content is returned.

404.Name: response404
404.Description: Consent not found or already revoked.

Response.Name: response
Response.Description: Consent successfully revoked. No content is returned.

Parameters.Name: consentId
Parameters.Description: The unique identifier for the consent to revoke.

Errors.ErrorMessage: Consent not found or already revoked.
